Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).
Put the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @rice vinegar{15%ml}, half the @honey{30%ml} and
half the @sambal paste{15%g} into a #medium bowl{}. Mix together.

TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and chopped) then pop onto a #cutting board{}
and use a #rolling pin{} to smack it a few times until split. Chop into roughly
2cm chunks. Add the cucumber to the bowl of marinade, toss to coat then set aside.

Pop the wedges onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle
over the @sesame seeds{7%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat,
then spread out in a single layer.

TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through. Meanwhile, pop the remaining @?sambal paste{} into a
#small bowl{} with the @mayonnaise{1/2} and @honey{10%ml}. Mix together.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}
or #cling film{}. Pop onto a cutting board, then give it a bash with the bottom
of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} into a
medium bowl or #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. In another
medium #shallow bowl{}, mix together the @cornflour{50%g} and @water{50%ml} for
the crumb. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then whisk until well combined. Dip
the chicken breasts into the cornflour mixture, then the breadcrumbs, ensuring
they are completely coated. Then pop the chicken onto a plate.

IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put a #large frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for
~{2-3%minutes} before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown and
cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat
as necessary. Once cooked, transfer the chicken breasts to a clean plate lined
with #kitchen paper{}. 

IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Drain the oil from your pan and pop back on medium-high heat. Lay in the
@British streaky bacon{4} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on
each side.

IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the @unsalted butter{20%g}, garlic and remaining honey to the pan and let it
melt. Coat the bacon, then remove from the heat.

When almost ready to serve, halve the @glazed burger bun{2} and pop into the
oven to warm for ~{2-3%minutes}. Spread a spoonful of @spicy mayo{} onto each
warmed bun base and top with the chicken and bacon. Spoon over some melted
honey garlic butter on the cut side of the bun tops before sandwiching shut.
Share out the wedges, and serve the cucumber in a bowl alongside. Enjoy!